      "title": "Quasifinite representations of a Lie algebra of Block type",
      "abstract": "AbstractLet B be the Lie algebra of Block type over C with basis { L \u03b1,i , C | \u03b1,i \u2208Z, i \u22121}and relations[ L \u03b1,i ,L \u03b2,j ]= ((i +1 )\u03b2 \u2212 (j +1 )\u03b1)L \u03b1 + \u03b2,i + j + \u03b1\u03b4 \u03b1 + \u03b2, 0 \u03b4 i + j, \u22122 C , [ C,L \u03b1,i ]=0. In this paper, itis proved that a quasi\ufb01nite irreducible B -module is a highest or lowest weight module. Furthermore,the quasi\ufb01nite irreducible highest weight modules are classi\ufb01ed and the unitary ones are proved tobe trivial. \uf6d9 2004 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved. 1. IntroductionBlock [1] introduced a class of in\ufb01nite dimensional simple Lie algebras over a \ufb01eld ofcharacteristic zero. Generalizations of Block algebras (usually referred to as Lie algebrasof Block type) have been studied by many authors (see, for example, [5,13,14,17\u201323]).Partially because they are closely related to the Virasoro algebra (and some of them aresometimes called Virasoro-like algebras [21]), these algebras have attracted some attentionin the literature. The structure theory of these algebras has been developed, however, theirrepresentation theory does not seem to be well-developed yet.In this paper, we study representations of the universal central extension"
